amming.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Is Subarrays Distinct Element Sum of Squares I good for interviews?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes — as a Easy problem it is a solid practice target. Pair it with related problems in the same pattern family for spaced repetition.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Where can I read the official statement?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Open the official LeetCode page for constraints and examples: https://leetcode.com/problems/subarrays-distinct-element-sum-of-squares-i/\"}}]}</script><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"HowTo\",\"name\":\"How to solve Subarrays Distinct Element Sum of Squares I\",\"description\":\"Original Easy explanation for Subarrays Distinct Element Sum of Squares I (LeetCode #2913). Pattern: dynamic programming. Time O(nlogn), space O(n). Multi-language solutions and interview tips.\",\"step\":[{\"@type\":\"HowToStep\",\"position\":1,\"text\":\"Read the official problem statement on LeetCode\"},{\"@type\":\"HowToStep\",\"position\":2,\"text\":\"Solve on paper / whiteboard first\"},{\"@type\":\"HowToStep\",\"position\":3,\"text\":\"Implement the dynamic programming, segment tree, fenwick tree, sorted list, and hash map approach\"},{\"@type\":\"HowToStep\",\"position\":4,\"text\":\"Verify edge cases from the checklist\"},{\"@type\":\"HowToStep\",\"position\":5,\"text\":\"State time and space complexity aloud\"},{\"@type\":\"HowToStep\",\"position\":6,\"text\":\"Compare with the AlgoForge reference solution\"},{\"@type\":\"HowToStep\",\"position\":7,\"text\":\"Schedule a revision session\"}]}</script><nav aria-label=\"Breadcrumb\" class=\"text-sm text-muted-foreground\"><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Home\",\"item\":\"https://algoforge.dev/\"},{\"@type\":\"List