 target. Pair it with related problems in the same pattern family for spaced repetition.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Where can I read the official statement?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Open the official LeetCode page for constraints and examples: https://leetcode.com/problems/subarrays-distinct-element-sum-of-squares-i/\"}}]}0:{\"rsc\":[\"$\",\"$1\",\"c\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"container-af py-8\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Article\\\",\\\"headline\\\":\\\"Subarrays Distinct Element Sum of Squares I\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Original Easy explanation for Subarrays Distinct Element Sum of Squares I (LeetCode #2913). Pattern: dynamic programming. Time O(nlogn), space O(n). Multi-language solutions and interview tips.\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/subarrays-distinct-element-sum-of-squares-i\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Organization\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"AlgoForge\\\"},\\\"publisher\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Organization\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"AlgoForge\\\"},\\\"datePublished\\\":\\\"2026-01-01\\\",\\\"dateModified\\\":\\\"2026-07-17\\\"}\"}}],[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$2\"}}],[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowTo\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"How to solve Subarrays Distinct Element Sum of Squares I\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Original Easy explanation for Subarrays Distinct Element Sum of Squares I (LeetCode #2913). Pattern: dynamic programming. Time O(nlogn), space O(n). Multi-language solutions and interview tips.\\\",\\\"step\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Read the official problem statement on LeetCode\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Solve on paper / whiteboard first\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Implement the dynamic programming, segment tree, fenwick tree, sorted list, and hash map approach\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":4,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Verify edge cases from the checklist\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":5,\\\"text\\\":\\\"State time and space complexity aloud\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":6,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Compare with the AlgoForge reference solution\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":7,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Schedule a revision session\\\"}]}\"}}],[\"$\",\"nav\",null,{\"aria-label\":\"Breadcrumb\",\"className\":\"text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Home\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Problems\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Subarrays Distinct Element Sum of Squares I\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/subarrays-distinct-element-sum-of-squares-i\\\"}]}\"}}],\"$L3\"]}],\"$L4\"]}],[\"$L5\"],\"$L6\"]}],\"isPartial\":false,\"staleTime\":300,\"varyParams\":null,\"buildId\":\"qYmpHdIWGSv0ZBoY8Y0Bn\"}\n3:[\"$\",\"ol\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",\"/\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[false,[\"$\",\"$L7\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"className\":\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\",\"children\":\"Home\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"/problems\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"aria-hidden\":true,\"className\":\"text-border\",\"children\":\"/\"}],[\"$\",\"$L7\",null,{\"href\":\"/problems\",\"className\":\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\",\"children\":\"Problems\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"/problems/subarrays-distinct-element-sum-of-squares-i\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"aria-hidden\":true,\"className\":\"text-border\",\"children\":\"/\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-foreground font-medium\",\"aria-current\":\"page\",\"children\":\"Subarrays Distinct Element Sum of Squares I\"}]]}]]}]\na:T29f3,// Time:  O(nlogn)\n// Space: O(n)\n\n#include <ext/pb_ds/assoc_container.hpp>\n#include <ext/pb_ds/tree_policy.hpp>\nusing namespace __gnu_pbds;\n\n// bit, fenwick tree, ordered set, math\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    int sumCounts(vector<int>& nums) {\n        static const int MOD = 1e9 + 7;\n\n        using ordered_set = tree<int, null_type, less<int>, rb_tree_tag, tree_order_statistics_node_update>;\n        ordered_set os;\n        unordered_map<int, vector<int>> idxs;\n        for (int i = size(nums) - 1; i >= 0; --i) {\n            idxs[nums[i]].emplace_back(i);\n        }\n        for (const auto& [_, v] : idxs) {\n            os.insert(v.back());\n        }\n        int result = 0;\n        int accu = ((static_cast<int64_t>(size(nums)) * size(os)) % MOD) * size(os) % MOD;\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(os); ++i) {\n            accu = ((accu - (static_cast<int64_t>(2 * i + 1) * *os.find_by_order(i) % MOD)) % MOD + MOD) % MOD;\n        }\n        BIT bit(size(nums));\n        for (const auto& x : os) {\n            bit.add(x, x);\n        }\n\n        const auto& update = [&](int x, int accu, int d) {\n            const int i = os.order_of_key(idxs[x].back());\n            accu = ((accu + d * (static_cast<int64_t>(size(nums)) * (2 * static_cast<int>(size(os)) - 1)\n                                 - static_cast<int64_t>(2 * i + 1) * idxs[x].back()\n                                 - 2ll * (bit.query(size(nums) - 1) - bit.query(idxs[x].back())))) % MOD + MOD) % MOD;\n            bit.add(idxs[x].back(), d * idxs[x].back());\n            return accu;\n        };\n\n        for (const auto& x : nums) {\n            result = (result + accu) % MOD;  // accu = sum(count(i, k) for k in range(i, len(nums)))\n            accu = update(x, accu, -1);\n            os.erase(idxs[x].back());\n            idxs[x].pop_back();\n            if (empty(idxs[x])) {\n                continue;\n            }\n            os.insert(idxs[x].back());\n            accu = update(x, accu, +1);\n        }\n        assert(accu == 0);\n        return result;\n    }\n\nprivate:\n    class BIT {\n    public:\n        BIT(int n) : bit_(n + 1) {  // 0-indexed\n        }\n        \n        void add(int i, int val) {\n            ++i;\n            for (; i < size(bit_); i += lower_bit(i)) {\n                bit_[i] = (bit_[i] + val) % MOD;\n            }\n        }\n\n        int query(int i) const {\n            ++i;\n            int total = 0;\n            for (; i > 0; i -= lower_bit(i)) {\n                total = (total + bit_[i]) % MOD;\n            }\n            return total;\n        }\n    \n    private:\n        int lower_bit(int i) const {\n            return i & -i;\n        }\n        \n        vector<int> bit_;\n        static const int MOD = 1e9 + 7;\n    };\n};\n\n// Time:  O(nlogn)\n// Space: O(n)\n// dp, segment tree, math\nclass Solution2 {\npublic:\n    int sumCounts(vector<int>& nums) {\n        static const int MOD = 1e9 + 7;\n\n        int result = 0, accu = 0;\n        unordered_map<int, int> lookup;\n        SegmentTree st(size(nums));\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(nums); ++i) {\n            const int j = lookup.count(nums[i]) ? lookup[nums[i]] : -1;\n            // sum(count(k, i)^2 for k in range(i+1)) - sum(count(k, i-1)^2 for k in range(i))\n            // = sum(2*count(k, i-1)+1 for k in range(j+1, i+1))\n            // = (i-j) + sum(2*count(k, i-1) for k in range(j+1, i+1))\n            accu = (accu + ((i - j) + 2ll * st.query(j + 1, i))) % MOD;\n            result = (result + accu) % MOD;\n            st.update(j + 1, i, 1);  // count(k, i) = count(k, i-1)+(1 if k >= j+1 else 0) for k in range(i+1)\n            lookup[nums[i]] = i;\n        }\n        return result;\n    }\n\nprivate:\n    class SegmentTree {\n    private:\n        static const int MOD = 1e9 + 7;\n\n    public:\n        explicit SegmentTree(\n            int N)\n         :  base_(N > 1 ? 1 << (__lg(N - 1) + 1) : 1),\n            lazy_(base_),\n            tree_(N > 1 ? 1 << (__lg(N - 1) + 2) : 2),\n            count_(size(tree_), 1) {\n\n            for (int i = base_ - 1; i >= 1; --i) { // added\n                count_[i] = count_[i << 1] + count_[(i << 1) + 1];\n            }\n        }\n\n        void update(int L, int R, const int val) {\n            L += base_;\n            R += base_;\n            // push(L);  // enable if range assignment\n            // push(R);  // enable if range assignment\n            int L0 = L, R0 = R;\n            for (; L <= R; L >>= 1, R >>= 1) {\n                if ((L & 1) == 1) {\n                    apply(L++, val);\n                }\n                if ((R & 1) == 0) {\n                    apply(R--, val);\n                }\n            }\n            pull(L0);\n            pull(R0);\n        }\n\n        int query(int L, int R) {\n            if (L > R) {\n                return 0;\n            }\n            L += base_;\n            R += base_;\n            push(L);\n            push(R);\n            int left = 0, right = 0;\n            for (; L <= R; L >>= 1, R >>= 1) {\n                if ((L & 1) == 1) {\n                    left = (left + tree_[L++]) % MOD;\n                }\n                if ((R & 1) == 0) {\n                    right = (tree_[R--] + right) % MOD;\n                }\n            }\n            return (left + right) % MOD;\n        }\n\n    private:\n        void apply(int x, const int val) {\n            tree_[x] = (tree_[x] + static_cast<int64_t>(val) * count_[x]) % MOD;  // modified\n            if (x < base_) {\n                lazy_[x] = (lazy_[x] + val) % MOD;\n            }\n        }\n\n        void pull(int x) {\n            while (x > 1) {\n                x >>= 1;\n                tree_[x] = (tree_[x << 1] + tree_[(x << 1) + 1]) % MOD;\n                if (lazy_[x]) {\n                    tree_[x] = (tree_[x] + static_cast<int64_t>(lazy_[x]) * count_[x]) % MOD;  // modified\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        void push(int x) {\n            for (int h = __lg(x) - 1; h > 0; --h) {\n                int y = x >> h;\n                if (lazy_[y]) {\n                    apply(y << 1, lazy_[y]);\n                    apply((y << 1) + 1, lazy_[y]);\n                    lazy_[y] = 0;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        int base_;\n        vector<int> tree_;\n        vector<int> lazy_;\n        vector<int> count_;  // added\n    };\n};\n\n// Time:  O(nlogn)\n// Space: O(n)\n// dp, segment tree, math\nclass Solution3 {\npublic:\n    int sumCounts(vector<int>& nums) {\n        static const int MOD = 1e9 + 7;\n\n        const auto& sum = [&] (const auto& x, const auto& y) {\n            return (x + y) % MOD;\n        };\n\n        int result = 0, accu = 0;\n        unordered_map<int, int> lookup;\n        SegmentTree<int> st(size(nums), sum, sum);\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(nums); ++i) {\n            const int j = lookup.count(nums[i]) ? lookup[nums[i]] : -1;\n            // sum(count(k, i)^2 for k in range(i+1)) - sum(count(k, i-1)^2 for k in range(i))\n            // = sum(2*count(k, i-1)+1 for k in range(j+1, i+1))\n            // = (i-j) + sum(2*count(k, i-1) for k in range(j+1, i+1))\n            accu = (accu + ((i - j) + 2ll * st.query(j + 1, i))) % MOD;\n            result = (result + accu) % MOD;\n            st.update(j + 1, i, 1);  // count(k, i) = count(k, i-1)+(1 if k >= j+1 else 0) for k in range(i+1)\n            lookup[nums[i]] = i;\n        }\n        return result;\n    }\n\nprivate:\n    template <typename T>\n    class SegmentTree {\n    private:\n        static const int MOD = 1e9 + 7;\n\n    public:\n        explicit SegmentTree(\n            int N,\n            const function<T(const T&, const T&)>& query_fn,\n            const function<T(const T&, const T&)>& update_fn)\n         :  base_(N > 1 ? 1 << (__lg(N - 1) + 1) : 1),\n            lazy_(base_),\n            tree_(N > 1 ? 1 << (__lg(N - 1) + 2) : 2),\n            count_(size(tree_), 1),\n            query_fn_(query_fn),\n            update_fn_(update_fn) {\n\n            for (int i = base_ - 1; i >= 1; --i) { // added\n                count_[i] = count_[i << 1] + count_[(i << 1) + 1];\n            }\n        }\n\n        void update(int L, int R, const T& val) {\n            L += base_;\n            R += base_;\n            // push(L);  // enable if range assignment\n            // push(R);  // enable if range assignment\n            int L0 = L, R0 = R;\n            for (; L <= R; L >>= 1, R >>= 1) {\n                if ((L & 1) == 1) {\n                    apply(L++, val);\n                }\n                if ((R & 1) == 0) {\n                    apply(R--, val);\n                }\n            }\n            pull(L0);\n            pull(R0);\n        }\n\n        T query(int L, int R) {\n            if (L > R) {\n                return T{};\n            }\n            L += base_;\n            R += base_;\n            push(L);\n            push(R);\n            T left{}, right{};\n            for (; L <= R; L >>= 1, R >>= 1) {\n                if ((L & 1) == 1) {\n                    left = query_fn_(left, tree_[L++]);\n                }\n                if ((R & 1) == 0) {\n                    right = query_fn_(tree_[R--], right);\n                }\n            }\n            return query_fn_(left, right);\n        }\n\n    private:\n        void apply(int x, const T val) {\n            tree_[x] = update_fn_(tree_[x], (static_cast<int64_t>(val) * count_[x]) % MOD);  // modified\n            if (x < base_) {\n                lazy_[x] = update_fn_(lazy_[x], val);\n            }\n        }\n\n        void pull(int x) {\n            while (x > 1) {\n                x >>= 1;\n                tree_[x] = query_fn_(tree_[x << 1], tree_[(x << 1) + 1]);\n                if (lazy_[x]) {\n                    tree_[x] = update_fn_(tree_[x], (static_cast<int64_t>(lazy_[x]) * count_[x]) % MOD);  // modified\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        void push(int x) {\n            for (int h = __lg(x) - 1; h > 0; --h) {\n                int y = x >> h;\n                if (lazy_[y]) {\n                    apply(y << 1, lazy_[y]);\n                    apply((y << 1) + 1, lazy_[y]);\n                    lazy_[y] = 0;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        int base_;\n        vector<T> tree_;\n        vector<T> lazy_;\n        vector<T> count_;  // added\n        const function<T(const T&, const T&)> query_fn_;\n        const function<T(const T&, const T&)> update_fn_;\n    };\n};\n\n// Time:  O(n^2)\n// Space: O(n)\n// hash table\nclass Solution4 {\npublic:\n    int sumCounts(vector<int>& nums) {\n        static const int MOD = 1e9 + 7;\n\n        int result = 0;\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(nums); ++i) {\n            unordered_set<int> lookup;\n            for (int j = i; j >= 0; --j) {\n                lookup.emplace(nums[j]);\n                result = (result + (static_cast<int64_t>(size(lookup)) * size(lookup) % MOD)) % MOD;\n            }\n        }\n        return result;\n    }\n};\nb:T1a18,# Time:  O(nlogn)\n# Space: O(n)\n\nimport collections\nfrom sortedcontainers import SortedList\n\n\n# bit, fenwick tree, sorted list, math\nclass Solution(object):\n    def sumCounts(self, nums):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type nums: List[int]\n        :rtype: int\n        \"\"\"\n        MOD = 10**9+7\n        class BIT(object):  # 0-indexed.\n            def __init__(self, n):\n                self.__bit = [0]*(n+1)  # Extra one for dummy node.\n\n            def add(self, i, val):\n                i += 1  # Extra one for dummy node.\n                while i < len(self.__bit):\n                    self.__bit[i] = (self.__bit[i]+val) % MOD\n                    i += (i & -i)\n\n            def query(self, i):\n                i += 1  # Extra one for dummy node.\n                ret = 0\n                while i > 0:\n                    ret = (ret+self.__bit[i]) % MOD\n                    i -= (i & -i)\n                return ret\n\n        def update(accu, d):\n            i = sl.bisect_left(idxs[x][-1])\n            accu = (accu + d*(len(nums)*(2*len(sl)-1) - (2*i+1)*idxs[x][-1] - 2*(bit.query(len(nums)-1)-bit.query(idxs[x][-1])))) % MOD\n            bit.add(idxs[x][-1], d*idxs[x][-1])\n            return accu\n\n        idxs = collections.defaultdict(list)\n        for i in reversed(xrange(len(nums))):\n            idxs[nums[i]].append(i)\n        result = 0\n        sl = SortedList(idxs[x][-1] for x in idxs)\n        accu = (len(nums)*len(sl)**2) % MOD\n        for i, x in enumerate(sl):\n            accu = (accu-(2*i+1)*x) % MOD\n        bit = BIT(len(nums))\n        for x in sl:\n            bit.add(x, x)\n        for x in nums:\n            result = (result+accu) % MOD  # accu = sum(count(i, k) for k in range(i, len(nums)))\n            accu = update(accu, -1)\n            del sl[0]\n            idxs[x].pop()\n            if not idxs[x]:\n                continue\n            sl.add(idxs[x][-1])\n            accu = update(accu, +1)\n        assert(accu == 0)\n        return result\n\n\n# Time:  O(nlogn)\n# Space: O(n)\n# dp, segment tree, math\nclass Solution2(object):\n    def sumCounts(self, nums):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type nums: List[int]\n        :rtype: int\n        \"\"\"\n        MOD = 10**9+7\n        # Template:\n        # https://github.com/kamyu104/LeetCode-Solutions/blob/master/Python/longest-substring-of-one-repeating-character.py\n        class SegmentTree(object):\n            def __init__(self, N,\n                         build_fn=None,\n                         query_fn=lambda x, y: y if x is None else x if y is None else (x+y)%MOD,\n                         update_fn=lambda x, y: y if x is None else (x+y)%MOD):\n                self.tree = [None]*(1<<((N-1).bit_length()+1))\n                self.base = len(self.tree)>>1\n                self.lazy = [None]*self.base\n                self.query_fn = query_fn\n                self.update_fn = update_fn\n                if build_fn is not None:\n                    for i in xrange(self.base, self.base+N):\n                        self.tree[i] = build_fn(i-self.base)\n                    for i in reversed(xrange(1, self.base)):\n                        self.tree[i] = query_fn(self.tree[i<<1], self.tree[(i<<1)+1])\n                self.count = [1]*len(self.tree)  # added\n                for i in reversed(xrange(1, self.base)):  # added\n                    self.count[i] = self.count[i<<1] + self.count[(i<<1)+1]\n\n            def __apply(self, x, val):\n                self.tree[x] = self.update_fn(self.tree[x], val*self.count[x])  # modified\n                if x < self.base:\n                    self.lazy[x] = self.update_fn(self.lazy[x], val)\n\n            def __push(self, x):\n                for h in reversed(xrange(1, x.bit_length())):\n                    y = x>>h\n                    if self.lazy[y] is not None:\n                        self.__apply(y<<1, self.lazy[y])\n                        self.__apply((y<<1)+1, self.lazy[y])\n                        self.lazy[y] = None\n\n            def update(self, L, R, h):  # Time: O(logN), Space: O(N)\n                def pull(x):\n                    while x > 1:\n                        x >>= 1\n                        self.tree[x] = self.query_fn(self.tree[x<<1], self.tree[(x<<1)+1])\n                        if self.lazy[x] is not None:\n                            self.tree[x] = self.update_fn(self.tree[x], self.lazy[x]*self.count[x])  # modified\n\n                L += self.base\n                R += self.base\n                # self.__push(L)  # enable if range assignment\n                # self.__push(R)  # enable if range assignment\n                L0, R0 = L, R\n                while L <= R:\n                    if L & 1:  # is right child\n                        self.__apply(L, h)\n                        L += 1\n                    if R & 1 == 0:  # is left child\n                        self.__apply(R, h)\n                        R -= 1\n                    L >>= 1\n                    R >>= 1\n                pull(L0)\n                pull(R0)\n\n            def query(self, L, R):\n                if L > R:\n                    return None\n                L += self.base\n                R += self.base\n                self.__push(L)\n                self.__push(R)\n                left = right = None\n                while L <= R:\n                    if L & 1:\n                        left = self.query_fn(left, self.tree[L])\n                        L += 1\n                    if R & 1 == 0:\n                        right = self.query_fn(self.tree[R], right)\n                        R -= 1\n                    L >>= 1\n                    R >>= 1\n                return self.query_fn(left, right)\n\n        result = accu = 0\n        sl = {}\n        st = SegmentTree(len(nums))\n        for i in xrange(len(nums)):\n            j = sl[nums[i]] if nums[i] in sl else -1\n            # sum(count(k, i)^2 for k in range(i+1)) - sum(count(k, i-1)^2 for k in range(i))\n            # = sum(2*count(k, i-1)+1 for k in range(j+1, i+1))\n            # = (i-j) + sum(2*count(k, i-1) for k in range(j+1, i+1))\n            accu = (accu+((i-j)+2*max(st.query(j+1, i), 0)))%MOD\n            result = (result+accu)%MOD\n            st.update(j+1, i, 1)  # count(k, i) = count(k, i-1)+(1 if k >= j+1 else 0) for k in range(i+1)\n            sl[nums[i]] = i\n        return result\n\n\n# Time:  O(n^2)\n# Space: O(n)\n# hash table\nclass Solution3(object):\n    def sumCounts(self, nums):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type nums: List[int]\n        :rtype: int\n        \"\"\"\n        MOD = 10**9+7\n        result = 0\n        for i in xrange(len(nums)):\n            lookup = set()\n            for j in reversed(xrange(i+1)):\n                lookup.add(nums[j])\n                result = (result+len(lookup)**2) % MOD\n        return result\n4:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-6 grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_280px] gap-10\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"article\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"header\",null,{\"className\":\"space-y-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm text-muted-foreground tabular-nums\",\"children\":[\"#\",2913]}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide bg-easy/15 text-easy\",\"children\":\"Easy\"}],false,[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":[\"~\",30,\" min\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"className\":\"text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight\",\"children\":\"Subarrays Distinct Element Sum of Squares I\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl\",\"children\":[\"Time \",[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"className\":\"text-foreground\",\"children\":\"O(nlogn)\"}],\" · \",\"Space \",[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"className\":\"text-foreground\",\"children\":\"O(n)\"}],\" · \",[\"$\",\"a\",null,{\"href\":\"https://leetcode.com/problems/subarrays-distinct-element-sum-of-squares-i/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"text-primary underline-offset-2 hover:underline\",\"children\":\"Official statement on LeetCode\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap gap-2\",\"children\":[[[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"dynamic-programming\",{\"href\":\"/topics/dynamic-programming\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide bg-primary/15 text-primary\",\"children\":\"dynamic programming\"}]}]],[[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"dynamic-programming\",{\"href\":\"/patterns/dynamic-programming\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"dynamic programming\"}]}],[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"segment-tree\",{\"href\":\"/patterns/segment-tree\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"segment tree\"}]}],[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"fenwick-tree\",{\"href\":\"/patterns/fenwick-tree\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"fenwick tree\"}]}],[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"sorted-list\",{\"href\":\"/patterns/sorted-list\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"sorted list\"}]}],[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"hash-map\",{\"href\":\"/patterns/hash-map\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"hash map\"}]}]],[]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap gap-2 pt-1\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L8\",null,{\"slug\":\"subarrays-distinct-element-sum-of-squares-i\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"cpp\",{\"href\":\"/problems/subarrays-distinct-element-sum-of-squares-i/cpp\",\"className\":\"text-sm text-primary hover:underline\",\"children\":\"cpp\"}],[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"python\",{\"href\":\"/problems/subarrays-distinct-element-sum-of-squares-i/python\",\"className\":\"text-sm text-primary hover:underline\",\"children\":\"python\"}]]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-10\",\"id\":\"solutions\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold mb-3\",\"children\":\"Solutions\"}],[\"$\",\"$L9\",null,{\"solutions\":{\"cpp\":{\"language\":\"C++\",\"languageSlug\":\"cpp\",\"filename\":\"subarrays-distinct-element-sum-of-squares-i.cpp\",\"code\":\"$a\",\"sourcePath\":\"C++/subarrays-distinct-element-sum-of-squares-i.cpp\"},\"python\":{\"language\":\"Python\",\"languageSlug\":\"python\",\"filename\":\"subarrays-distinct-element-sum-of-squares-i.py\",\"code\":\"$b\",\"sourcePath\":\"Python/subarrays-distinct-element-sum-of-squares-i.py\"}}}]]}],[\"$Lc\",\"$Ld\",\"$Le\",\"$Lf\",\"$L10\",\"$L11\",\"$L12\",\"$L13\",\"$L14\",\"$L15\"],\"$L16\",\"$L17\",\"$L18\",\"$L19\",\"$L1a\",\"$L1b\"]}],\"$L1c\"]}]\n5:[\"$\",\"script\",\"script-0\",{\"src\":\"/_next/static/chunks/259rkrk9l2f9c.js\",\"async\":true}]\n6:[\"$\",\"$L1d\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$1e\",null,{\"name\":\"Next.MetadataOutlet\",\"children\":\"$@1f\"}]}]\n20:T44d,<h2>What is Subarrays Distinct Element Sum of Squares I?</h2>\n<p><strong>Subarrays Distinct Element Sum of Squares I</strong> (LeetCode #2913) is a <strong>Easy</strong> problem that primarily trains <strong>dynamic programming</strong>.</p>\n<h3>How to think about it</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Restate the goal</strong> in your own words before coding.</li>\n<li>Work a <strong>tiny example</strong> by hand so the invariant becomes obvious.</li>\n<li>Identify the <strong>pattern</strong> — this problem aligns with <strong>dynamic programming, segment tree, fenwick tree, sorted list, and hash map</strong>.</li>\n<li>Only then translate the idea into code.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Why this problem matters</h3>\n<p>It builds core muscle memory you will reuse on harder variants.\nOfficial solution notes mention: DP, Segment Tree, BIT, Fenwick Tree.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>AlgoForge explanations are original teaching notes. Always open the <a href=\"https://leetcode.com/problems/subarrays-distinct-element-sum-of-squares-i/\">official problem statement on LeetCode</a> for constraints and examples.</p>\n</blockquote>\nc:[\"$\",\"section\",\"beginner\",{\"id\":\"beginner\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Beginner Explanation\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$20\"}}]]}]\n21:T50c,<h2>Interview approach for Subarrays Distinct Element Sum of Squares I</h2>\n<h3>Opening (30–60 seconds)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Clarify inputs/outputs and edge cases (empty input, single element, duplicates, overflow).</li>\n<li>State a <strong>brute force</strong> so the interviewer knows you can solve it naively.</li>\n<li>Propose the <strong>optimal direction</strong> tied to <strong>dynamic programming, segment tree, fenwick tree, sorted list, and hash map</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Core solution narrative</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Define the <strong>state</strong> you track (pointers, DP cell, set membership, stack top, etc.).</li>\n<li>Explain the <strong>transition</strong> when you process the next element.</li>\n<li>Call out <strong>time</strong> (O(nlogn)) and <strong>space</strong> (O(n)) before coding.</li>\n<li>Code cleanly; narrate variable names.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>What interviewers listen for</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Correctness on edge cases</li>\n<li>Complexity honesty</li>\n<li>Ability to discuss <strong>trade-offs</strong> (e.g., hash map space vs. sort + two pointers)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Follow-up questions they may ask</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Can you solve it with less memory?</li>\n<li>What if the input stream is infinite / doesn't fit in RAM?</li>\n<li>How would tests look for adversarial inputs?</li>\n</ul>\nd:[\"$\",\"section\",\"interview\",{\"id\":\"interview\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Interview Walkthrough\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$21\"}}]]}]\n22:T45b,<h2>Optimized solution notes</h2>\n<p>The reference solutions on AlgoForge target <strong>O(nlogn)</strong> time and <strong>O(n)</strong> space.</p>\n<h3>Pattern focus: dynamic programming, segment tree, fenwick tree, sorted list, and hash map</h3>\n<p>Use the pattern as a checklist:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>dynamic programming</strong> — confirm the invariant holds after each step</li>\n<li><strong>segment tree</strong> — confirm the invariant holds after each step</li>\n<li><strong>fenwick tree</strong> — confirm the invariant holds after each step</li>\n<li><strong>sorted list</strong> — confirm the invariant holds after each step</li>\n<li><strong>hash map</strong> — confirm the invariant holds after each step</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Multiple methods appear in the source solutions — compare them and explain when each is preferable.</p>\n<h3>Implementation tips</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Prefer readable names over micro-optimizations in interviews.</li>\n<li>Extract helpers only when they clarify (e.g., expand-around-center, DFS visit).</li>\n<li>After AC-level logic, re-scan for off-by-one and null checks.</li>\n</ul>\ne:[\"$\",\"section\",\"optimized\",{\"id\":\"optimized\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Optimized Approach\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$22\"}}]]}]\nf:[\"$\",\"section\",\"complexity\",{\"id\":\"complexity\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Complexity Analysis\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Complexity</h2>\\n<table>\\n<thead>\\n<tr>\\n<th>Measure</th>\\n<th>Bound</th>\\n</tr>\\n</thead>\\n<tbody>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Time</td>\\n<td><strong>O(nlogn)</strong></td>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Space</td>\\n<td><strong>O(n)</strong></td>\\n</tr>\\n</tbody>\\n</table>\\n<h3>How to justify this in an interview</h3>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Time:</strong> count loops, map/set operations, and recursive branching; state average vs worst case if relevant.</li>\\n<li><strong>Space:</strong> include hash maps, recursion stack, and output allocation when the problem asks for it.</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>If your implementation differs from the reference, re-derive big-O from <em>your</em> code — never memorize a complexity you cannot defend.</p>\\n\"}}]]}]\n10:[\"$\",\"section\",\"common-mistakes\",{\"id\":\"common-mistakes\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Common Mistakes\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Common mistakes on Subarrays Distinct Element Sum of Squares I</h2>\\n<ol>\\n<li><strong>Skipping edge cases</strong> — empty collections, single-element inputs, max constraints.</li>\\n<li><strong>Wrong invariant</strong> for dynamic programming, segment tree, fenwick tree, sorted list, and hash map — updating state too early or too late.</li>\\n<li><strong>Mutating input unexpectedly</strong> when the problem forbids it.</li>\\n<li><strong>Off-by-one</strong> in windows, ranges, or binary search bounds.</li>\\n<li><strong>Ignoring overflow / precision</strong> for integer arithmetic problems.</li>\\n<li><strong>Overengineering</strong> — jumping to an advanced structure when a simpler approach works.</li>\\n</ol>\\n\"}}]]}]\n11:[\"$\",\"section\",\"alternatives\",{\"id\":\"alternatives\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Alternative Approaches\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Alternatives</h2>\\n<p>The source file includes more than one method. Compare:</p>\\n<ol>\\n<li><strong>Primary optimized path</strong> — best complexity for typical interviews.</li>\\n<li><strong>Secondary approach</strong> — often brute force, sorting-based, or space-optimized variant.</li>\\n</ol>\\n<p>Practice articulating <strong>when</strong> you would pick each (constraints, readability, follow-ups).</p>\\n\"}}]]}]\n12:[\"$\",\"section\",\"edge-cases\",{\"id\":\"edge-cases\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Edge Cases\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Edge cases checklist</h2>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Minimum input size</li>\\n<li>Maximum input size / time limits</li>\\n<li>Duplicates and already-sorted input</li>\\n<li>Negative numbers / zeros (if applicable)</li>\\n<li>Disconnected structures (graphs/trees)</li>\\n<li>Single path vs branching recursion depth</li>\\n</ul>\\n\"}}]]}]\n13:[\"$\",\"section\",\"pattern-recognition\",{\"id\":\"pattern-recognition\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Pattern Recognition\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Spotting this pattern</h2>\\n<p>Signal phrases that point to <strong>dynamic programming, segment tree, fenwick tree, sorted list, and hash map</strong>:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Sorted input or ability to sort without changing the answer class</li>\\n<li>Need for contiguous subarray / substring → consider sliding window</li>\\n<li>Need for O(1) membership → hash set/map</li>\\n<li>Optimal substructure + overlapping subproblems → DP</li>\\n<li>Connectivity / components → graph DFS/BFS or Union-Find</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>Primary topics: <strong>dynamic programming</strong>.</p>\\n\"}}]]}]\n14:[\"$\",\"section\",\"follow-ups\",{\"id\":\"follow-ups\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Follow-up Interview Questions\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Follow-ups</h2>\\n<ol>\\n<li>How does the solution change if the input is a stream?</li>\\n<li>Can you solve it in-place?</li>\\n<li>What if duplicates must be handled differently?</li>\\n<li>How would you parallelize the approach?</li>\\n<li>Design tests that would break a buggy implementation.</li>\\n</ol>\\n\"}}]]}]\n15:[\"$\",\"section\",\"practice\",{\"id\":\"practice\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\"